I believe that this problem is not tied to which fields to display. As long as it hits the maximum display width on a Confluence page, it will auto cut-off for the display. 

A quick workaround: After adding the JIRA issues macro, the *column width* for each display can be adjusted by your *mouse cursor*. Another strong reason why Atlassian have included the option *JIRA Field Columns to display* is because we would want to give our users the extra privilege to display possibly the 5 most important columns where it is also adjustable.

